definition: to divide/to separate/to distribute/to allocate/to distinguish (good and bad)/part or subdivision/fraction/one tenth (of certain units)/unit of length equivalent to 0.33 cm/minute (unit of time)/minute (angular measurement unit)/a point (in sports or games)/0.01 yuan (unit of money)
one/1/single/a (article)/as soon as/entire/whole/all/throughout/"one" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 1)/also pr. [yao1] for greater clarity when spelling out numbers digit by digit

sentences.english: Nurse Yaima Milian examines a patient at Baptist Health of South Florida in Miami Health care is one-sixth of the economy.
sentences.chinese: 醫療保健佔據整個經濟的六分之一。

sentences.english: The worst-case scenario says that a third to a half of all marriages end in divorce.
sentences.chinese: 最糟糕的案例顯示六分之一的婚姻結束於離婚。

sentences.english: One in six said they shouldn't have children, said Bergeson.
sentences.chinese: 六分之一的人認爲他們不應該要孩子。

sentences.english: Health care is one-sixth of the economy.
sentences.chinese: 醫療保健佔據整個經濟的六分之一。

sentences.english: One Slim Jim gives you more than one-sixth of the sodium your body needs in a day.
sentences.chinese: 一條瘦吉姆爲你提供每日所需鈉離子的六分之一。

sentences.english: Throughout Zong 's life, the most glorious is to recover 1/6 of the national territories.
sentences.chinese: 縱觀左宗棠的一生，最輝煌的是收復六分之一的國土。

sentences.english: So, it's roughly one sixth for the homework.
sentences.chinese: 家庭作業大概就佔六分之一。

sentences.english: The next biggest producer, Japan, will make just one-sixth of what China is expected to produce.
sentences.chinese: 全球第二大產鋼國日本的產量僅爲中國的六分之一。

sentences.english: We still have one-in-six Americans either unemployed or underemployed.
sentences.chinese: 我們還有六分之一的美國人失業或未充分就業。
